      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's just not about \"support\" or \"resources.\" it's more like... the fundamental way i'm built is just wrong for this world. i spend every single day just performing a version of myself that people can tolerate, and i'm just so incredibly tired of it. it feels like there's no version of \"me\" that actually fits. it's like i'm running on a dead battery and no matter how much i try, it just won't hold a charge. it's just constant drag.",
